<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3168] Arena allocation causes excessive flushing on small heaps</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3168</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;adding allocator.size() to Memtable.getLiveSize has two problems:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) it double-counts allocated parts of regions&lt;br/&gt;
2) it makes the size of an empty memtable the size of a single region&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(2) is a particular problem because flushing a nearly-empty memtable will not actually free up much memory &amp;#8211; we just trade one almost-empty region, for another.  In testing, I even saw this happening to the low-traffic system tables like LocationInfo.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
